ess private methods, but it seems maybe not. I'm curious about whether there’s a built-in API in pekko-http-core that can address Http2AlpnSupport without requiring a stream, since all actual HTTP/2 TLS operations go through streams.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Troubleshooting native test execution**\\\\n\\\\nI’m considering testing with the JVM and running into some limitations on skipping native execution. Using `@EnabledOnJre` isn't an option. I'm thinking about potentially using a dynamic class loading pattern, but that seems irrelevant. I wonder if I should write a test referencing active class via generated bytecode instead. There's this idea of separating the test source set, but I’m not sure that would help either. I'll need to check the dynamic coverage report after a failure to learn more about what went wrong.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_sa5swZuKU4vJCKWeXD5Ax6fM|fc_0775c31a3e99d9ff0169fb3b8e75d0819590060776453e22fa\", \"name\": \"read\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/org.apache.pekko/pekko-http-core_3/1.3.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json\", \"limit\": 100}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 12333, \"output\": 1245, \"cacheRead\": 53760, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 67338, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1778072441497, \"responseId\": \"resp_0775c31a3e99d9ff0169fb3b7a0eb08195822bb06c4e000809\"}}\n3907:[tool-exec] start id=call_sa5swZuKU4vJCKWeXD5Ax6fM|fc_0775c31a3e99d9ff0169fb3b8e75d0819590060776453e22fa name=read args={\"path\": \"tests/src/org.apache.pekko/pekko-http-core_3/1.3.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json\", \"limit\": 100}\n3912:        \"covered\" : false,\n3919:      \"coveredCalls\" : 0,\n3926:      \"coveredCalls\" : 0,\n3930:[recv] {\"type\": \"message