ssert on Jetty; if it succeeds, I'll ensure that SSLParameters contain \"h2.\"\n3968:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Evaluating test coverage**\\n\\nI’m thinking about success and coverage in testing. If there's no coverage, can it be considered a fail? I wonder if coverage reports might be misleading if the JavaVersion initializes from a previous test. Setting the -D option at launch seems to ensure that early initialization uses version 1.8, which is good. I should use clientSetApplicationProtocols and check the results. If it fails, I can assert on Jetty; if it succeeds, I'll ensure that SSLParameters contain \\\"h2.\\\"\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0775c31a3e99d9ff0169fb3b970c3c81958a9a9e6f60b91f29\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp-zvH4g2_XWBYMC0oHxpAD6-QCH2QNNBucGqDXUyoKYFYTOolnNyaOlb2alUWfITsBDM40Zry2B65NQAHBQdnpxAGJKguRrzlnaRZiQC5ElPtqt3GSPz4e4fRIRFcOb5n3aAtnZFefWHTT96l3NSBHzKyN67IFAez3W4VZC22huv6xvOD5pbvA7RHSizlYFUhF7xnGCl9v_3-lx2PRmgK3WolG4mzLVzCQJG0YfjJiKbmX7XoGg7Z8n1YAE93apZpCi73GhLvOIOi1UZUeaegkwq33lhYH_87bRQnufUX9pD9Mx82NoCrLVyrRH8QbmQtSdetsGhHxzegRZv5ajxeVVVlGXxLrMQaFvBQvjXKmSUW3r02KmWCnJBd6b8SRDFkXcsfddlIFNISvBbOY9vCchtbHHeVm-H7ttQk3vg865bVNPFxGqkTBbr4sRp5Uk6b2JUjs5GRijJLXX94IYzfspQ2OmX8xw6tHazNVFhAak6fUQkUdsq3clkS6gqVZzGsg-J7p2rpoz7iu0w4IP-rL-fiKTv_XSiFqcNGwWTz4hOn1JFqshVkq6kefzCA8KKTnQJ3ElSxtf8FLapdKcUNxwWS8IUvHZTqRH7g0wCG3ifc7a2SzyrZQdOXIfrKNE5nd2JFrJPmyqWZwuaeMEIOxy8rJxasUyLLqpBFRl8tiaz_hLzOcx8RbNlgwSsMovNsFiw5B830Fzo7kL61fKImOQPJAVLqz0Z-3BapzYFiJI-rl_Lpzurby2m1QDsNVebZtuVXJZ3vyBx0MTKUkl9qh-vCr5q_qqPVrEqJx-hR4WUYOaehOAxeBQZLWV3sT1sEnvf2Z6W6aPZrdEQVTwu0ayw9zoVNyzSzEzso_8ztUoF7P_DfXibouPe0qWhhyIgYWFTN8gS_TkkY8RvLwhuCEnJdkCP8KoW8VbX8ZEvpzKMDOcXrtIq9EmORxLgVmSEbyQ4M-9P8qb2vEOEoQClPgSTityetLpGU5_I5JoYmly6NRbZSqZVblVu-8Dssug4d9UYOGvYSQ9ySwVoZYlm-XIck7WQUQ6ubllgZSJ8y9UnTaUeeYBXvyAO6axr0n3bli2YydWf_-I