ic SSLEngine enableForServer(SSLEngine engine) {\\\\n        return Http2AlpnSupport.enableForServer(engine, protocol -> BoxedUnit.UNIT);\\\\n    }\\\\n}\\\\n\\\", \\\"newText\\\": \\\"final class Http2AlpnSupportInvoker {\\\\n    private Http2AlpnSupportInvoker() {\\\\n    }\\\\n\\\\n    static void setClientApplicationProtocols(SSLEngine engine) {\\\\n        Http2AlpnSupport.clientSetApplicationProtocols(engine, new String[] {\\\\\\\"h2\\\\\\\"});\\\\n    }\\\\n}\\\\n\\\"}]}}], \\\"api\\\": \\\"openai-responses\\\", \\\"provider\\\": \\\"OCA\\\", \\\"model\\\": \\\"gpt-5.5\\\", \\\"usage\\\": {\\\"input\\\": 886, \\\"output\\\": 3325, \\\"cacheRead\\\": 67072, \\\"cacheWrite\\\": 0, \\\"totalTokens\\\": 71283, \\\"cost\\\": {\\\"input\\\": 0, \\\"output\\\": 0, \\\"cacheRead\\\": 0, \\\"cacheWrite\\\": 0, \\\"total\\\": 0}}, \\\"stopReason\\\": \\\"toolUse\\\", \\\"timestamp\\\": 1778072469373, \\\"responseId\\\": \\\"resp_0775c31a3e99d9ff0169fb3b9611c08195bc93457013fca4e8\\\"}}\\n3974:[recv] {\\\"type\\\": \\\"turn_end\\\", \\\"message\\\": {\\\"role\\\": \\\"assistant\\\", \\\"content\\\": [{\\\"type\\\": \\\"thinking\\\", \\\"thinking\\\": \\\"**Evaluating test coverage**\\\\n\\\\nI’m thinking about success and coverage in testing. If there's no coverage, can it be considered a fail? I wonder if coverage reports might be misleading if the JavaVersion initializes from a previous test. Setting the -D option at launch seems to ensure that early initialization uses version 1.8, which is good. I should use clientSetApplicationProtocols and check the results. If it fails, I can assert on Jetty; if it succeeds, I'll ensure that SSLParameters contain \\\\\\\"h2.\\\\\\\"\\\", \\\"thinkingSignature\\\": \\\"{\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"rs_0775c31a3e99d9ff0169fb3b970c3c81958a9a9e6f60b91f29\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"reasoning\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"encrypted_content\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"gAAAAABp-zvH4g2_XWBYMC0oHxpAD6-QCH2QNNBucGqDXUyoKYFYTOolnNyaOlb2alUWfITsBDM40Zry2B65NQAH