t. I need to solve the patch class detection problem first.\\\\n\\\\n**Analyzing Java Toolchain Options**\\\\n\\\\nIt seems like this repo is using the Java toolchain version 21, not Graal. Changing `java.specification.version` at launch could be risky, so I’m wary of that. I’m thinking of forcing the JavaVersion object initialization without early initialization, potentially using an isolated classloader. I wonder if we could separate loading for the Pekko classes while addressing the library on the classpath. Forking a new Java process seems convoluted, plus the native test constraints add complexity. Maybe direct reflective methods are an option, but there are limitations there too.\\\\n\\\\n**Exploring Java Reflection Options**\\\\n\\\\nI'm considering whether `sun.security.ssl` is really a library or not. Maybe there's a way to utilize `Class.getDeclaredMethods()` in a lambda for this Java helper. I think I might have to manipulate the `JavaVersion.majorVersion` field after initialization to set it to 8. Using `sun.misc.Unsafe` or VarHandle could work, but getting access to Unsafe typically requires reflection, which is tricky. I wonder if the public `JavaVersion` package has a static final int for majorVersion that might be helpful.\\\", \\\"thinkingSignature\\\": \\\"{\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"rs_0775c31a3e99d9ff0169fb3bea525881958f828d5e63418c5b\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"reasoning\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"encrypted_content\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"gAAAAABp-zwDkbucTyoiJuX6W-nq5V0yHzRn3d9DVgRB3WMyxrRNopapRoyB-ZiJC-caH7NiNrStqlzANrfX8lURljbAs_Wap0PFTkhAs2klX1_TdFmxaAD93oNdBl4x_axa3qWAl23C-WN4L6hbAdFLybNsWA4T499XlnsJMSgFwM8qY1GAc99q0ijsZnHP94c63Cl_u85nilLFT43CSchn9xJqrIhWt1NXhNmpKwfPOYAPPjoJXNPR049RPeAQNgmEjRO-C7SbqaIxbWvGJqKNsfn_q0rTjlB1LJ8FGkLNuyuTeY2hIrMb7wDduA4C143o07ImjqloaCkt8oRUcQ4C7MpPpQClXtRjohh-2t1tjpxBpyW50vzlp57HyHPE4otPfQY1oQZJYd0QObwV38aZAEstoIh6z7DMsaF77kddBGu-Q6IToIuvZKHylk2bg585NSxYmzuyk6TgbD1NqVT2SXy3v4Hy-EBGLSR_TPkg6Zuvpk8fm4JvMRV3Q7y4awctjwncSy6-9n